4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses the safety of the model and proposes a framework to quantify the robustness of neural networks, which is relevant to cryptography and security. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a framework based on Satisfiability Modulo Theory (SMT) solvers to quantify the robustness of neural networks, which is relevant to systems and control.
